## MEDIUM Path Execution

1. Determine target branch: `<target-branch>` is the PR base (`--base` or `dev`), or current branch if working directly
2. Acquire lock on `<target-branch>`
3. Update run state to status="executing" (add `"worktree":"<name>"` if using worktree)
4. Assess risk: if changes are risky or user requests isolation, use `/worktree:create` for isolated environment
5. Otherwise, work on current branch
6. Implement the feature/fix
7. Create PR to target base via `/pr:create --base <base-branch>` (default `dev`, or as provided by `--base`)
8. Mark completion and release lock:
   - Remove lock: `rm -f .claude/run/locks/<target-branch>.lock`
   - Update state: `jq '.status="completed"' .claude/run/$RUN_ID.json > .claude/run/$RUN_ID.json.tmp && mv .claude/run/$RUN_ID.json.tmp .claude/run/$RUN_ID.json`
   - Update current: `echo '{"type":"MEDIUM","base":"<base-branch>","status":"completed"}' > .claude/run/current.json`
   - Print `[ORC_COMPLETED]`
